author: @Kabbinj
text: All of the issues you show can be dealt with by making proper prompts. And no, two lines of text is not a proper prompt.  Write clear, unambiguous instructions, with examples, using domain specific terms.  You need to be an expert in the field you are building prompts for, do not expect it to just magically know what you think.

author: @mindcache5650
text: Bard prompt answer :  Bard can write Python code. In fact, Bard can write code in over 20 programming languages, including Python, C++, Java, JavaScript, and TypeScript. Bard can generate code for a variety of tasks, such as:  Calculating mathematical expressions Sorting and searching data Manipulating strings Generating random numbers Creating functions and classes Writing loops and conditional statements  Yes, it is possible that Bard will be able to be your data scientist and data analyst in the future. As a large language model, Bard is constantly learning and evolving. It is already able to perform many tasks that are typically done by data scientists and data analysts, such as cleaning data, writing SQL queries, and generating reports.
